---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const description = "Use HIPAA to challenge collection agency authorization and remove medical collections. Step-by-step strategy with validation letter template.";
---

<Base title="HIPAA Medical Debt Removal Strategy — CreditCookbook" description={description} posterTitle="HIPAA REMOVAL" posterLabel="// 04 — use HIPAA to challenge collections">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">// hipaa removal strategy</span>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 16px;">The HIPAA removal method.</h2>
      <p style="max-width: 64ch; margin-bottom: 32px; opacity: 0.7;">HIPAA governs how healthcare providers share your medical information. If a provider sent your information to a collection agency without proper authorization, you can leverage this to challenge the collection.</p>

      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 24px;">The process (5 steps)</h3>
      <ol style="margin-left: 24px; line-height: 2.5; margin-bottom: 32px;">
        <li><strong>Pay the original provider directly.</strong> Contact the hospital or doctor and pay the original bill — not the collection agency. Get a receipt.</li>
        <li><strong>Request a HIPAA validation letter.</strong> Ask the collection agency to prove legal authorization to collect and that the provider shared your information in compliance with HIPAA.</li>
        <li><strong>File a HIPAA complaint with HHS OCR.</strong> If the agency cannot produce authorization documentation, file at hhs.gov/ocr.</li>
        <li><strong>Dispute with the credit bureaus.</strong> Cite the HIPAA violation. The bureau must verify — and if the agency is under investigation, they often cannot.</li>
        <li><strong>Follow up with method-of-verification.</strong> If the bureau verifies, demand to know how. Many use automated e-OSCAR, which is insufficient.</li>
      </ol>

      <hr class="rule" style="margin: 40px 0;" />

      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 16px;">HIPAA Validation Letter Template</h3>
      <div class="mono-block" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
[YOUR NAME]
[YOUR ADDRESS]
[YOUR CITY, STATE ZIP]

[DATE]

[COLLECTION AGENCY NAME]
[COLLECTION AGENCY ADDRESS]

RE: Request for HIPAA Authorization Documentation
Account: [ACCOUNT NUMBER]
Original Creditor: [HEALTHCARE PROVIDER NAME]

To Whom It May Concern,

I am requesting documentation demonstrating that you
have valid authorization to collect on the above-referenced
medical debt, and that the original creditor disclosed my
protected health information to you in compliance with
the HIPAA Privacy Rule (45 CFR 164.502 and 164.508).

Specifically, I am requesting:
1. A copy of the authorization form signed by me
   permitting disclosure to your agency.
2. Documentation of your Business Associate Agreement
   with the original provider.
3. Proof that you have a legal right to collect this debt.

If you cannot provide this documentation within 30 days,
I request that you cease all collection activity and remove
this account from all credit reporting agencies.

Sincerely,

[YOUR NAME]
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h4 style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Important notes</h4>
        <ul style="margin-left: 24px; line-height: 2;">
          <li>Pay the original provider — never the collection agency</li>
          <li>Get a receipt showing the debt is paid at the source</li>
          <li>File the HHS complaint at hhs.gov/ocr/privacy/hipaa/complaints</li>
          <li>This method is for unpaid medical collections only</li>
          <li>If the collection is under $500, it should not appear at all</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
